  <div class="upgrade-inner reveal">
    <p class="eyebrow">Want the Full Tradition?</p>
    <h2>Add the 30-day herbal drinks</h2>
    <p>Food is one pillar of Zuo Yue Zi; the herbal drinks are another. Fifteen formulas, stage by stage, one cup a day — no sugar, no carbs, and nothing that works against the way you're eating this month.</p>
    <a href={orderUrl('local_lowcarb', locale)} class="btn btn-primary">Add the herbal drinks — {usd(products.herbal_drink.price * 30)}</a>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ FAQ ============ -->
<section class="faq-band" id="faq">
  <Svg28 class="botan faq-botan" aria-hidden="true" />
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Good Questions</p>
      <h2>Before you decide</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-list reveal">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What exactly is left out?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Rice and grains at lunch and dinner, the breakfast porridge, the two daily desserts, and the sweet daily healing drink. That's it.</p><p>Everything else stays: the breakfast egg dish, the lunch soup, the Taiwanese postpartum soup and dinner soup, entrées, and warm vegetables at both meals — all cooked from scratch and delivered fresh daily. The <a href="https://file.jingmommy.com/f/Meal_Comparison_Chart.pdf" download>Meal Comparison Chart</a> shows every plan side by side.</p></div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Without the rice, is it still enough food?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Fair question — and yes, on paper it's our leanest plan: no rice, no porridge, no dessert. But fewer items doesn't mean less filling. Protein and slow-simmered soups sit with you longer than a bowl of rice does, so most moms find a day of Low Carb keeps them satisfied between meals. You still get three warm meals a day, with an entrée and vegetables at both lunch and dinner.</p><p>If you'd like to see for yourself before committing, the <a href="https://file.jingmommy.com/f/Menu.pdf" download>Full Menu</a> lists every dish, and a single day is {usd(products.local_lowcarb_1d.price)}.</p></div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Is this a weight-loss plan?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>No. This is a Zuo Yue Zi recovery plan, and it exists to nourish you — not to make you smaller. We don't make weight or body promises, and we'd be wary of anyone who did during your first month postpartum.</p><p>Mothers usually choose this plan because they're managing blood sugar, because heavy carbs simply don't sit well with them, or because low-carb is already how they eat. If you have a medical reason for eating this way, please loop in your own doctor — and we're glad to share the full menu with them.</p></div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Can I add the herbal drinks?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes — they're an optional add-on at <strong>{usd(products.herbal_drink.price * 30)} for the 30 days</strong>, one cup a day. Fifteen formulas that follow the traditional recovery sequence, stage by stage. They contain no sugar, so they sit comfortably alongside a low-carb month.</p></div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How does delivery work, and when should I order?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>In our regular service area, meals are delivered fresh every day and we aim to reach your door before noon — actual times shift with traffic and routes, so an exact hour isn't guaranteed. Remote areas receive every-other-day delivery, and an additional delivery fee may apply. Refrigerate your meals on arrival, and heat them thoroughly before eating.</p><p>Order at least a month before your due date if you can. The week your baby arrives, you won't have the bandwidth to compare plans or fill out forms — and you shouldn't have to. Your start date can be adjusted once the baby comes.</p></div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ TASTE CTA ============ -->
